        <heading>Connecticut HUSKY Plan</heading>
        <section eId="sec_17a_544">
          <num>17a-544</num>
          <heading>(Formerly Sec. 17-206e). Placement of patient in seclusion or mechanical restraint. Medication not to be used as substitute for habilitation</heading>
          <subsection eId="17a_544__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>No patient may be placed involuntarily in seclusion or a mechanical restraint unless necessary because there is imminent physical danger to the patient or others and a physician so orders. A written memorandum of such order, and the reasons therefor, shall be placed in the patient's permanent clinical record within twenty-four hours.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17a_544__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <heading>Medication shall not be used as a substitute for an habilitation program</heading>
